The paper deals with the deployment of service function chains in a network, which involves selecting and instantiating virtual network functions, placing VNF instances, and routing traffic through them. This falls under the category of network architecture and protocols, which is covered by cs.NI. The paper also addresses optimization problems related to the selection, placement, and routing of VNFs, which can be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the formulation of a mixed integer programming (MIP) model and the development of a local search heuristic, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with security issues related to service function chaining, which can be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
